    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-03-31T05:09:48+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-31T05:09:48+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-30T18:39:48Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-30T18:39:48Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system over the Tasman sea extends a weak ridge over SA. A trough over central WA extends over southwest SA, and is forecast to move across the west and south later Tuesday, pushing into the northeast of SA on Wednesday. Another high pressure system is expected to become established south of the Bight late in the week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW002" description="Yorke Peninsula" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-03-31T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-01T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-30T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-31T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny day. Medium chance of showers this evening. Winds north to northeasterly 25 to 35 km/h increasing to 45 km/h before turning west to northwesterly 20 to 25 km/h in the evening. Daytime maximum temperatures around 30.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">High</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 10:20am to 4:20pm, UV Index predicted to reach 7 [High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-01T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-02T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-31T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-01T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers in the north, medium chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm in the north in the morning. Winds westerly 15 to 25 km/h turning south to southwesterly during the day. Overnight temperatures falling to around 16 with daytime temperatures reaching the mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-02T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-03T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-01T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-02T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">The chance of morning fog. Mostly sunny day. Winds southeast to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h becoming southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h during the afternoon then tending southerly 15 to 25 km/h during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 12 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-03T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-04T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-02T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-03T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower in the south in the morning and afternoon. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds southerly 15 to 20 km/h turning southeasterly 25 to 35 km/h during the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to around 13 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
